Calculating cost estimation for AWS resources created using terraform

Step1: List of all AWS resources created in the region ME-CENTRAL-1(UAE)

#Terraform Command to check all aws resources created
--terraform state list

#Output
aws_internet_gateway.devopstest_igw
aws_key_pair.devopstest_kp
aws_route_table.devopstest_public_rt
aws_route_table_association.devopstest_public_assoc
aws_security_group.devopstest_pub_sg
aws_subnet.devopstest_pub_subnet
aws_vpc.devopstest_vpc
local_file.private_key
tls_private_key.devopstest_kp

Step2: Identify the AWS pricing for each resource

| Resource                    | Count | Pricing Details              | Monthly Cost |
| --------------------------- | ----- | ---------------------------- | ------------ |
| t3.micro EC2                | 1     | $0.0125 per hour (us-east-1) | ~$9          |
| EBS gp3 8GB                 | 1     | $0                           | ~$0          |
| VPC, subnet, SG             | 1     | Free                         | $0           |
| Data transfer (1M requests) | 1     | Assume 1GB/month free tier   | $0           |

free upto 30 GiB of EBS storage, 2 million I/Os, 1 GB of snapshots, and 100 GB of bandwidth to the internet
3,000 IOPS free and $0.0061/provisioned IOPS-month over 3,000
Multiply EC2 hourly rate by 24 × 30 (~720 hours) for monthly cost.

Cost Estimatation Monthly
Total	≈ $9 / month

For 1M requests:
Still the same cost (EC2 is fixed price)

No per-request cost as long as you stay in same region
